Welcome to the Forecasting Projects Delivery Guide. This document serves as a step-by-step manual to assist teams in successfully executing forecasting projects, particularly during Proof-of-Concept (PoC) phases with clients. It provides guidelines, checklists, references to documentation and code bases, and best practices from project initiation to delivering results.

## Introduction

This guide is designed to streamline the process of delivering forecasting projects by providing a standardized approach. It should serve to ensure consistency across projects, improves efficiency, and enhances the quality of deliverables to clients.

- Lessons learnt: At Teknosa PoC requirement document, they had asked for two different demand forecast results: 8 weeks and 3 months (monthly) of store x SKU. During our initial meetings we figured out that they will actually only use 8 weeks forecasts as a basis for evaluation of PoC.  Some advanced calculations like cannibalization-substitution or competitor price sensitivity are almost impossible to run within the POC timeline. Make sure the scope you are working with is acceptable. If the client insists on those outputs, we can always mitigate by generating some reports that reflect our approach.
